Bring a pan of water to the boil and boil the new potatoes for 8-10 minutes, or until tender, and the beans for 3-4 minutes. Drain.Gently heat the butter in a non-stick frying pan. Season the trout fillet and pan fry for 2-3 minutes on each side.Transfer the trout to a serving plate. Spoon the new potatoes and beans alongside and drizzle with the melted butter to serve.